<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#contains> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "range is lrmlmm:RuleStatement, LegalRuleML's own formal common superclass of ConstitutiveStatement and PrescriptiveStatement (see statement.rdf in the OASIS metamodel RDFS modules), not an ad-hoc class of ours. Used for both constitutive statements (definitions, eligibility rules) and prescriptive statements (rights, exceptions). Fixed 2026-07-22: an earlier draft wrongly restricted this to ConstitutiveStatement only; fixed 2026-07-23: gave it a real range instead of leaving it open, which had made it resolve to owl:Thing in WebVOWL." .
