# 
# http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#ConstitutiveStatement
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#ConstitutiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#ConstitutiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement> .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#ConstitutiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a statement that defines a term or establishes eligibility, without itself granting or restricting conduct." .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#ConstitutiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constitutive Statement" .
# 
# http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#Jurisdiction
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#Jurisdiction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#Jurisdiction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the country or supranational body a legal Expression applies in; ISO code, or 'un' for WIPO treaties." .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#Jurisdiction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Jurisdiction" .
# 
# http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#PrescriptiveStatement
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#PrescriptiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#PrescriptiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement> .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#PrescriptiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a statement that grants, restricts, or otherwise governs conduct, e.g. a right or an exception." .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#PrescriptiveStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Prescriptive Statement" .
# 
# http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "a Legal Statement modelled by a Legal Rule; the formal LegalRuleML superclass of ConstitutiveStatement and PrescriptiveStatement, per the OASIS metamodel RDFS module (not part of the HTML spec's prose, only its machine-readable RDFS)." .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Rule Statement" .
<http://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/ns/v1.0/metamodel#RuleStatement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://docs.oasis-open.org/legalruleml/legalruleml-core-spec/v1.0/os/rdfs/statement.rdf> .
# 
# http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Expression
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Expression> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Expression> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "one specific dated version of a Work (FRBR Expression), e.g. the 2000 text of the Irish Copyright Act." .
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Expression> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Expression" .
# 
# http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Work
<http://purl.org/vocab/frbr/core#Work> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
