# https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#Copyright
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#Copyright> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#Copyright> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the bundle of rights a Work carries; which specific acts it covers is given via :includesAct." .
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#Copyright> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Copyright" .
# 
# https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#ExceptionKind
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#ExceptionKind> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#ExceptionKind> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "the same Copyright Ontology (Garcia & Gil, JURIX 2008) lists seven exceptions: Quotation, Education, Information, Official Act, Private Copy, Parody, Temporary Reproduction. PrivateUseException and ParodyException match exactly (Private Copy, Parody); ResearchException, CriticismReviewException and NewsReportingException are only approximate matches to Education, Quotation and Information respectively, not identical in scope, flagged here rather than assumed equivalent." .
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#ExceptionKind> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Exception Kind" .
<https://w3id.org/wipo-ip#ExceptionKind> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> <https://rhizomik.net/html/~roberto/papers/rg-losw08.pdf> .
